## Step 5: End-to-End Repro (Old Adapter Line Only)

1. Build cases from fallback-pass HumanEval runs:
```bash
python scripts/build_rag_cases_from_fallback.py \
  --runs_root episodes/humaneval_runs \
  --dataset HumanEval \
  --out_path data/derived/rag/cases.jsonl
```

2. Build fine-tuning dataset and splits:
```bash
python scripts/build_finetune_dataset.py \
  --cases_path data/derived/rag/cases.jsonl \
  --out_dir data/derived/finetune \
  --seed 42 \
  --train_ratio 0.8 \
  --val_ratio 0.1
```

3. Train LoRA (old adapter path):
```bash
python scripts/train_lora_peft.py \
  --model_name_or_path models/hf/qwen2.5-coder-1.5b-instruct \
  --train_file data/derived/finetune/humaneval_slm_fix_pairs.cleaned.train.jsonl \
  --eval_file data/derived/finetune/humaneval_slm_fix_pairs.cleaned.val.jsonl \
  --output_dir data/derived/finetune/qwen1.5b_lora_fix
```

4. Evaluate adapter on selected HumanEval tasks:
```bash
python scripts/run_lora_humaneval_eval.py \
  --model_name_or_path models/hf/qwen2.5-coder-1.5b-instruct \
  --adapter_path data/derived/finetune/qwen1.5b_lora_fix \
  --task_ids HumanEval/0,HumanEval/7 \
  --max_seq_len 512 \
  --max_new_tokens 256 \
  --timeout_s 5
```

---

## Final Process Summary

Old adapter pipeline was:
1. Collect fallback-pass HumanEval fix episodes into case memory.
2. Transform cases into supervised `input` -> `output` code-fix pairs.
3. Split dataset (21 train / 2 val / 4 test).
4. Fine-tune Qwen2.5-Coder-1.5B with PEFT LoRA to `qwen1.5b_lora_fix`.
5. Evaluate generated code on HumanEval tasks using adapter-attached inference.

This is the complete old-adapter LoRA process currently evidenced in this repository.
